The PRS 516 is truly a pioneer watch that will never go out of style. T100.417.11.031.00

product_name: Tissot Tradition Rose Gold/Brown Leather Men's Watch
description: A slim case doesn’t mean we’ve compromised on style – or on design. Whether you prefer a dark or light dial, a leather strap or a metal bracelet, you’ll find the honest impact you’re looking to make with the Tissot Tradition Quartz collection. The watch expresses purity of design and is easy to read without being imposing. This is a watch collection that is sure to have many fans. T063.610.36.038.00

product_name: Tissot Couturier Automatic Chronograph Black Leather Men's Watch
description: Just as the creations of the world's great fashion designers rely on the perfect mix of fabric and cut, the Tissot Couturier timepieces blend elegant lines with materials to match. These watches express their made-to-measure character through their uncompromising attention to detail. These promise to outlive any fashion whim and stand the test of time. T035.627.16.051.00

A blend of carefully selected whiskies from all around the world, matured in a combination of ex-sherry and ex-bourbon casks, and then finished further in Mizunara Oak. This unique Japanese whisky is made with a 1:1 ration of malt to grain. Nose:  Notes of butter, coconut, mint, grass, old oak and a pinch of pepper Palate:  Slightly Oily with floral influences and hints of Chinese incense, butter and vanilla. Finish:  Short to Medium. Smooth, fragrant, sweet and earthy with sandalwood and vanilla spice Alcohol:  43%

product_name: The Glenlivet 12 Yo Single Malt Scotch Whisky 1L 40%
description:
The Glenlivet 12 Year Old Single Malt Scotch Whisky represents the signature style of The Glenlivet distillery. This iconic Single Malt is matured in European and American oak casks. The double oak maturation process imparts vanilla notes and gives The Glenlivet 12 Year Old its distinctive smoothness. Fruity and exceptionally well-balanced The Glenlivet 12 Year Old has a delicate yet complex character.
 Nose: Fruity, summer-like fragrances Taste: Well-balanced and fruity with intense pineapple notes

Selected with only the finest malt whiskies uniquely chosen to celebrate the Year of the Dragon. Aged more than 15 years in Sherry and Bourbon casks. Finished in Mizunara oak barrels, adding an unparalleled oriental elegance to this special edition spirit. All-natural ingredients and without coloring and other additives. A true expression of fine craftsmanship. A 2020 World Whisky Awards Category Winner. The Shinobu Dragon Year edition is a testament to its distinguished taste and quality. Tasting Notes: Nose: Fresh oak, vanilla, and floral notes, with a subtle touch of sandalwood. Palate: A refined mix of ripe fruits and lemon zest, with hints of leather and a blend of cinnamon and ginger. Finish: Long, rich finish with oak and fruity undertones, lightly accented by sandalwood. Alcohol:  43%

product_name: The Jelly Bean Factory 36 Flavour Gourmet Mix Tube 175g
description: The Jelly Bean Factory are the best sharing snack – but only if there’s enough to share. This tube contains 36 huge flavors, can you guess which flavor? The gourmet beans from The Jelly Bean Factory are made with 100% natural flavors and no artificial colors. The Jelly Bean Factory assortment is gluten free, and gelatine free.
Amazing big orange flavor that's so amazing, it's amazing.
Arnott's Tim Tam Classic Dark biscuits are made with a mouth-watering combination of crunchy biscuit, luscious dark chocolate centre, wrapped in a smooth dark chocolate coating.

Charles Tanqueray created the world’s finest London Dry Gin in 1830 and it is made today to the same classic, timeless recipe. Tanqueray No. Ten was created with this heritage in mind and set the standard as one of the very first ultra-premium gins.
 Tanqueray No. TEN Gin is distilled four times with Tanqueray’s standard gin botanicals of refreshing juniper, peppery coriander, aromatic angelica and sweet liquorice. Whole citrus fruits, including limes, oranges and pink grapefruit are then added with chamomile flowers to Tiny Ten, the still from which the liquid gets its name.

TOKI, Japanese for “Time”, is a vivid blend of Yamazaki and Hakushu Single Malt whisky and Chita Single Grain whisky. Fifth Generation Chief Blender, Shinji Fukuyo, challenges the conventional hierarchy between malt and grain whisky, highlighting the quality of the Chita grain whisky not as a base but in equal standing to the Hakushu and Yamazaki malts. Basil, green apple, and honey on the nose, with grapefruit, green grapes, peppermint and thyme on the palate.  A subtly sweet and spicy finish with a hint of vanilla, oak, white pepper, and ginger. Alcohol:  43%

Chita is a single grain whisky was made with diverse unblended
whisky brewing techniques and master craftsmanship
developed over many years at the Chita Distillery in Aichi
Prefecture. It features a light taste and delicately sweet fragrance.
The bottle design features black calligraphy that expresses
the distinctive qualities of Japanese whisky, set on a white
Japanese washi paper label representing the light flavor. Alcohol: 43%

Talisker 10 Years Old - The classic stalwart of the Talisker family. The perfect companion for when the day is done, smooth, smoky with a comforting afterglow.A classic Island dram from the Isle of Skye. Aged for a minimum of 10 years in American oak casks, this welcome member of Diageo's Classic Malts series has been recognised numerous times for its excellence.

product_name: Talisker Dark Storm Single Malt Scotch Whisky 1L Travel Exclusive
description: Talisker Dark Storm Single Malt Scotch Whisky is matured in heavily-charred oak casks for an intensely smoky flavour, designed to capture the wild, untamed spirit of a full-blown storm at sea. Tasting notes:A whisky with extra spice and smoke, matured in heavily charred casks. Alcohol:  45.8%

Introducing Talisker Surge, a Global Travel Exclusive offering from single malt brand Talisker. The first Talisker variant aged in 100% bourbon casks making it uniquely rich spiced and vibrant.   Made by the sea; flashes of surging spice and rich honeyed berries electrify the palate, while rolling smoke rumbles underneath. Liquid lightning that stirs the soul and sets pulses racing. 
 Taste:  Flashes of surging spice and rich, honeyed berries electrify the palate, while rolling smoke rumbles underneath, before a delicious chili bite surges forward. Liquid lightning that stirs the soul and sets pulses racing. Country of origin:  Great Britain 
 Ingredients:  Water, Alcohol, Barley, Colouring
with colourant
Manufacturer information: Diageo Scotland Limited,Lochside Place 11-12,EH12 9HA Edinburgh,GB Alcohol:  45.8% 
 Warnings:  Drink responsibly Storage conditions:  Store in a cool dry place.

Created by Charles Tanqueray in 1830, Tanqueray London Dry Gin is made today according to the same classic, timeless recipe. Tanqueray London Dry Gin is distilled four times and has the perfect balance of four classic gin botanicals – refreshing juniper, peppery coriander, aromatic angelica and sweet liquorice. It is best enjoyed with tonic water, plenty of ice and a wedge of lime, but can be used as a great base for a wide range of cocktails.
This Chardonnay is well balanced with citrus and white peach characters, creamy undertones from oak maturation and a long satisfying finish. Alcohol: 13.5%

Tanqueray Flor de Sevilla is a unique distilled gin made with Sevilla orange essences and other fine botanicals. Inspired by Charles Tanqueray’s original recipes and the ripening oranges growing on the trees in sun-drenched SEVILLE, the result is a perfect balance of the uniquely bittersweet taste of Seville oranges balanced with the complexity of Tanqueray London Dry Gin. It is best served with Premium tonic and a squeeze wedge of orange.
 Tanqueray's founder, Charles Tanqueray, was an innovator and pioneer in pursuit of the world's finest gin. In this pursuit he sourced botanicals from all around the world and created over 300 recipes. It is thought that his travels to the sun-soaked groves of Spain in the 1860s inspired the creation  of a unique gin liqueur using Seville oranges.
Back in the 1830s, Charles Tanqueray was not afraid to mix up brave ideas in his own unique style. He invented a gin which is still celebrated to this day. The perfect mix of ingenuity, heritage and hard work.   Tasting notes: Made with bittersweet Seville oranges for a fruitful and zesty taste. 41.3% Alcohol

The Aromantiques Chardonnay displays tantalising aromas of fresh apple blossom, jasmine, white peach, nectarine and almonds bringing this elegantly structured Chardonnay to life. This is a light bodied, wine with fresh, vibrant flavours of passionfruit, nectarine, peach and hints of citrus. Alcohol:  12.5%

Tanqueray No. Ten Grapefruit and Rosemary harnesses the definitive taste of Tanqueray No. Ten, spotlighting the fresh, sweet and juicy taste of pink and white grapefruit, balanced with notes of juniper before finishing with subtle hints of enchanting, woody rosemary Alcohol:  45.3%
Tanqueray Malacca Gin is based on a recipe developed by Charles Tanqueray dating back to 1839. Botanicals include cinnamon, clove, nutmeg and cardamom but the exact botanicals remain a secret.

Tanqueray Rangpur Distilled Gin was first created in 2006 by adding rangpur, an exotic citrus fruit from India with the zestiness of lime and the juiciness of mandarin oranges, together with ginger and bay leaves to Tanqueray’s premium London Dry Gin. The latter is still made today according to the same classic, timeless recipe that Charles Tanqueray created in 1830. It is distilled four times to remove any traces of neutral grain spirit and to allow the added flavours of a perfect balance of four classic gin botanicals – refreshing juniper, peppery coriander, aromatic angelica and sweet liquorice – to shine through. 

The result of adding rangpur, ginger and bay leaves to the original premium product is an easy-drinking gin with a citrus twist.  
Back in the 1830s, Charles Tanqueray was not afraid to mix up brave ideas in his own unique style. He invented a gin which is still celebrated to this day. The perfect mix of ingenuity, heritage and hard work.  Tasting notes: Rangpur – an exotic citrus from India – ginger and bay leaves are added to Tanqueray gin. 41.3% Alcohol

Tanqueray Blackcurrant Royale is a sumptuous and unique distilled gin made with French blackcurrants and vanilla notes, elevated with a black orchid inspired flavour and balanced with the four classic London Dry botanicals. Alcohol: 41.3%

Two-Fold is an approachable whisky crafted to be enjoyed any way you like. Two-Fold is a spirit that folds together Australian barley and wheat, fully matured in red wine barrels from our famed Australian wine regions. Tasting notes: Nose / Bright red berries coated in buttery vanilla spice. Palate / Imagine a smooth, rich caramel dessert balanced by tropical fruit. Finish / Delicate and long. A delicious, dry finish from a faded sweetness. Mix with / Tonic and garnish with a wedge of ruby grapefruit. Alcohol: 40% Starward Whisky Two-Fold 1L is Travel Exclusive Size

"Solera was our very first Starward whisky. Made using the traditional solera process means there is a drop of our very first whisky in every bottle. Matured in Australian Apera barrels, this whisky is a bona fide Starward Australian take on a traditional whisky.  Tasting notes: Nose / Bright tropical and orchard fruits, caramel and vanilla. Palate / Toasty caramel and creme brûlée, banana, figs and sweet spice. Finish / Juicy and full with a lingering dry spice." Alcohol: 43% Starward Whisky Solera 1L is Travel Exclusive Size
The Aromantiques GSM combine seductive cherry blossom, black plum and cinnamon in a masterful blend of McLaren Vale Grenache, Langhorne Creek Shiraz and Barossa Valley Mataro. Alcohol:  14.5%

Award winning pinot noir rose from marlborough in new zealand is full of intensity and flavour. flavours of mandarin, watermelon and strawberry with floral characteristics and a fresh finish. winner of best still rose award at the sydney international wine competition 2016, so you know it's going to be good.
The Aromantiques Rosé pair fragrant Clare Valley Grenache and Shiraz to uncover aromas of wild strawberries, succulent watermelon and freshly picked white flowers. Alcohol:  11%

St Agnes is a double distilled, pot-still brandy, prepared from specially crafted base wines. St. Agnes then rests for many years in small oak casks to ensure pure clean perfection. An Australian classic.

A stunning Grenache from 50+ year old vines. This wine is soft, fresh and fleshy with intense blueberry and goji berry fruits. The palate has great depth and length of flavour with a soft, long and finely spiced finish. Alcohol:  14.5%

Integrated elegant oak intermingled with ripe mulberry and plum fruit characters. This wine has great depth, richness and structure all coming to the fore with an elegant, long finish. Alcohol:  14.5%

The St Hugo wines showcase deep respect for the grapes grown on our sites by turning them into wines with structure, power and elegance. The wines are crafted to be part of your celebrations with loved ones all over the world – from their vineyards to your table. The cool climate and the warm rolling hills of the Eden Valley create wines distinctive in their character, displaying wonderful aromatics, elegance, complexity and finesse. Each vintage St Hugo's winemakers select some of the best fruit from the Eden Valley vineyards to create the St Hugo Eden Valley Chardonnay. Delicate green in colour, the wine has aromas of white peach and lemon curd with hints of citrus blossom on the nose. On the palate it is well balanced with refreshing flavours of lemon zest and white nectarines, creating a wine of great elegance.  Alcohol:  13%
This is an enticing wine with green apple, ripe pear and plush nectarine fruit characters combining with a satisfying hint of spice. Alcohol:  13%

Pale gold with vibrant lime hues, the wine has fragrant white florals, green lime and lemon pith. The palate is intense and pure with great length, showcasing flavours of grapefruit and green peppercorn balanced by taut acidity.  Such a great riesling year in Eden Valley. Perfumed and floral with a powdery bath-salts aroma and a spicy mix suggesting a racy palate is coming. Beautifully balanced and precise palate with a very long finish. Distinct lemon scents on the nose with a trace of lime. The palate has such a lovely acid integration. It's a pristine and pure riesling made with a minimalist approach to achieve the wine style. - Ray Jordan, The West Australian- 94 Points Alcohol:  11%
St Remy VSOP is a rounded, balanced spirit that is easy to drink. With its light and subtle nose, St Remy VSOP is excellent served as an aperitif or in cocktails.  Alcohol:  40%
The Aromantiques Pinot Gris has delightful aromas of fresh honeysuckle, green pear and honeydew melon. This is a sophisticated and vibrant drop. Alcohol:  12.5%

Multi-award-winning across the globe, St-Rémy XO is a rich and complex brandy. Its French aromatic intensity remains true to the style of the House. Intense and aromatic. Subtle notes of wood and vanilla are enriched with flavours of gingerbread, candied apricots, dates, figs and nuts. The taste is subtly spicy and offers a long finish. Offering multiple layers of flavours that make it remarkable to critics and connoisseurs alike, St-Rémy XO can be enjoyed neat, on ice or in classic cocktails. Alcohol:  40%

product_name: St Hallett Garden Of Eden Shiraz 750ml
description: The allure of raspberry jube and violet pastilles, intertwined with subtle hints of fennel seed and refreshing mint, adding depth and complexity to the bouquet. Opening with delicate floral notes reminiscent of violets and subtle notes of choc-mint and fennel seed. The palate unfolds into a briary spice, with the juiciness of raspberry pie sprinkled with a hint of cinnamon spice. The rich, opulent palate envelops your senses and fills your mouth, finishing long with a dense driving tannin. Alcohol:  13.5%

With every vintage our winemaking team learns more about the influence of the site on the flavour and quality of the wines. The Lindner family established St Hallett in 1944 on a property they had owned since the late 1800’s, focusing on their butchery business, with only a small amount of wine made for local sales. The Butcher’s Cart was used by the Linder Family for a daily sales trip throughout the Barossa with a range of meats available for purchase. Alcohol: 13.5%

St Hugo Vetus Purum Shiraz is a very deep purple with bright hues. The nose offers mocha, liquorice and raspberry in perfect balance. Intense and fleshy with a combination of dark berry fruits and a brightness of flavour. Ebenezer is renowned for the balance it maintains whilst also producing full flavoured and structured wines. The oak maturation supports the wine with spice and sweet tannin and has also allowed it to soften and open up. Alcohol:  14.9%

Over the years, our winemakers have frequently identified the black clay soil vineyards in a blind line up. This prevailing sense of place has inspired us to release a wine make entirely from fruit grown in this unique soil type.  The sweetness of ripe red cherries evolves on the palate, offering a touch of natural sweetness that's both comforting and vibrant. The interplay of exotic spice then takes centre stage, adding a subtle complexity that keeps you engaged with each sip. Alcohol:  14.5%

A luscious bouquet of fresh strawberries, white stone fruit and summer blossoms. Vibrant and succulent on the palate with an abundance of fresh strawberries and cream, rose petal and white peach that fill the senses, while clean cut acidity gives this Dry Rosé gorgeous length. The finish is fine and elegant with lingering flavours of raspberry, strawberry and a subtle savoury hint. Alcohol:  12.5%

St Hallett Gamekeeper’s range acknowledges the role of the Gamekeeper in maintaining a healthy balance to a property’s wildlife. Barossa and great Shiraz have become synonymous around the world and St Hallett is committed to both. Black fruits, mulberry and cherry interplay with toasted spice notes which flow seamlessly across the soft luscious palate and the finish is highlighted by a fine coating tannin. Alcohol:  14%

product_name: St Hugo Wine Australia Barossa Valley Grenache Shiraz Mataro 750ml
description: A ripe, juicy Grenache Shiraz Mataro which showcases some of Barossa’s best varietals in a balanced, food-friendly wine. Vibrant crimson with purple hues. Raspberry and spice with a subtle floral lift and background hints of cedar. Soft red and dark berry fruit with chalky tannins and a line of acidity which provides great length. Alcohol:  13%

The wine was first released in 1994, in honour of Stuart Blackwell, winemaker for more than three decades and a tireless contributor to the St Hallett story. The fruit is sourced predominately from Northern Barossa with the red brown clay soils creating wines with hallmark characteristics of black plum, cherries and dark chocolate. his full-bodied, rich and opulent wine is perfectly structured to ensure the wine will age gracefully throughout the years. Alcohol:  14%

It was a leap of faith which inspired a small group of European settlers to leave their homeland and seek opportunities of the Barossa ink 1842. A contemporary classic and a crowd favourite, Faith Shiraz is a vibrant and expressive example of Barossa Shiraz; accessible, juicy and fruit drive.  The sweetness of ripe red cherries evolves on the palate, offering a touch of natural sweetness that's both comforting and vibrant. Alcohol:  14%

A superb wine - perfectly blended to create a seamless, deep and complex blend with silky tannins and excellent cellaring potential. Rich plum flavours are complemented by a subtle coco notes and smooth structural oak. Plush, firm tannin and fresh acidity support the line and length of the wine to bring balance and vitality. Alcohol:  14.2%

Originally from the St Hallett Old Block vineyard, this wine was first made by Robert O’Callaghan and Stuart Blackwell in 1980. To qualify for Old Block Shiraz, the vineyards must be planted on their own rootstock and be more than 50 years old. The oldest vineyard used to create the 2019 Old Block was planted in 1870 whilst the youngest 1936, with an average of close to 100 years.  Alcohol:  14%

A selection of thirteen vineyards sourced from a diverse spread of sub regions ranging from near Williamstown in the far south to Ebenezer in the far north of the Barossa were utilised in the wine. Vineyards are concentrated in the far south and north of the Barossa Valley to drive the style required for St Hugo. The diversity of this fruit sourcing is to achieve the “power” from low yielding, mature Shiraz vines and “elegant” parcels from vineyards showing more restraint and structure. The vintage has yielded a wine of precision and concentration with effortless aging assured. Spiced blue fruits, fine boned tannins with fully immersed barrel complexity. Alcohol:  14.5%

With a crimson garnet colour and a nose filled with fresh mulberries, this wine is ready to drink now, but can be cellared for up to two years. The palate is rich and savoury, bursting with juicy flavours of blood plums and red liquorice. Tied together with layers of chalky dark chocolatey tannins, this rich and fruity wine flows to a smooth lingering finish. Enjoy this wine with something suitably Spanish: tomato-based Paellas, Iberico Jamon and roasted vegetables.

product_name: St Hugo Vetus Purum Coonawarra Cabernet Sauvignon, Australia 750ml
description:
Named in honour of the two fine winemaking principles Hugo Gramp embedded on the St Hugo crest – Vetus, meaning ancient, and Purum, meaning pure – the Vetus Purum wines represent the pinnacle of the St Hugo collection.

Already beautifully integrated, this wine could continue to develop for more than 20 years if cellared under ideal conditions.
 Harmony and balance are immediately apparent in this elegant, medium to full-bodied wine. The palate is assertive yet refined, with concentrated flavours of blackcurrant, berry and olive supported by subtle cedar spice from the oak. This is a premium Cabernet Sauvignon reflecting the unique terroir and pristine environment of the Coonawarra.

The squealing pig marlborough sauvignon blanc is a light straw with subtle grassy green hue. the nose is salivatingly crisp like a summer salad bursting with punchy tropical fruit and fresh herbs. the palate is practically exploding out of the glass it has so much energy bright and refreshing with layers of green pineapple and passionfruit. tangy citrus notes lead to a photo focused finish and delicious minerality.

A vibrant and beautifully textured expression of Sauvignon Blanc. This wine is elegantly structured with seductive passionfruit and green apple flavours, fresh herbaceous notes and a subtle touch of minerality. Certified Vegan Friendly. Alcohol:  12%

The wine has a mouth filling lusciousness, densely packed with generous plum and dark cherry fruit flavours along with subtle floral violet characters and a smack of vanilla underlying the opulent oak expression. Alcohol: 14.5% 
   Critics
  Rating: For the Masterstroke series fruit has been sourced from Coonawarra (Cabernet Sauvignon), McLaren Vale (Shiraz) and then back to their traditional Clare Valley home for the classic Australian Cabernet - 93 Points Angus Hughson.  A hot and dry vintage in McLaren Vale in this wine has created a robust and chewy red. Deeply coloured, it shows brooding blackberry and blueberry fruits with some rocky and white pepper complexity topped by toasted coconut oak. That is followed by a dense and spicy palate with sweet fruits showing underlying power that continues through to a good finish with drying tannins. It is quite a complex McLaren Vale style that will drink well over the medium term.

Shiraz delivers rich and plump dark plum to the mid palate whilst blackcurrent, dark chocolate and mint characters from the Cabernet Sauvignon drives the finish.  Overall a sublimely complex and multi layered wine. Critics Rating: Taylors have always hung their hat on cabernet sauvignon, but it’s interesting how often the classic Aussie blend of cabernet with shiraz comes up trumps. 2017 Vintage - 95 Points - The colour is deep red-purple and there are lifted aromas of dried herbs including thyme, mint, sage … indeed, a full bouquet. The palate is elegant, medium-full bodied, with enlivening acidity, and a certain sinewy mouth-feel. Very appealing balance and length. The mint is subtle and effective. Huon Hooke
Rich expressive flavours of cassis, mulberry and a hint of eucalypt. French oak maturation adds touches of dark chocolate, cedar and spice. Alcohol:  14.5%

The wine has delicious, haunting flavours of blackcurrant, mint and dark chocolate around a finely tuned and classy tannin structure. Critics Rating: A stylish, well made, deep crimson wine with lovely fresh varietal fruit characters of cassis and mint. Fleshy and flavoursome in the mouth with vibrant tannins. Tasting Panel Winestate Magazine
This is a lighter style red wine with juicy red fruit flavours of raspberry and strawberry along with hints of cinnamon spice. Alcohol:  14.5%
A refreshing Rosé crafted in the Provence style with vibrant red fruits and crisp acidity. Minimal time on skins gives a pale salmon colour and an elegant finish.  Alcohol: 12.5%
An elegant, perfumed expression of the variety, this wine is well structured, full of juicy red fruit and violet characters, superbly balanced with smooth tannins. Alcohol:  14.5%

Family-owned and operated, taylors wines rests on the principle that the finest wines are those made with the greatest dedication and care. this limited edition label celebrates their heritage and the commitment of three generations of the taylor family dedicated to making fine australian wine.
nose:
rich blackcurrant, subtle spice, tomato leaf and a touch of eucalyptus.
palate:
fine and elegant tannins, well balanced, and complex, with a lingering finish.

This pinnacle release Cabernet Sauvignon is crafted from the very finest fruit selection and is entirely estate grown and bottled on the Taylor family estate in the Clare Valley, South Australia. Tasting Notes: Color: A dark red-black core framed by a crimson rim. Nose:  The wine is attractively scented with wild berry and bramble hints backgrounded by light chocolate and mint notes with a subtle smoky cigar air from extended premium oak maturation. Palate: The wine delivers a focused, upfront berry and summer fruits profile that jumps straight to the centre of attention and is counterbalanced by a mouth-watering freshness. There is a ripe and highly integrated tannin and oak firmness to the focused, long finish. This wine has lovely dimensions and a poised, elegance and depth that reflects it’s carefully selected provenance, vinification and cellaring. Alcohol:  14.5%

Silky textured with exceptional length and flavours of peach, nectarine and subtle cashew nuances from quality French oak. Tasting Notes: Color: At release, the wine is a youthful pale straw colour with vibrant green hue to the edges. Nose: The wine has ripe white peach aromas along with hints of tropical fruit and subtle creamy oak. Enticing sweet spice and savoury cashew nut from the French oak add complexity to the bouquet. Palate: This is a medium-bodied yet sumptuous wine with an enjoyable creaminess to the mid-palate. Flavours of juicy white fleshed stone fruit are evident along with cleansing citrus at the finish which has wonderful persistence and length from the use of quality French oak. Alcohol:  13.5%

Hedonistic and tightly focused, this exceptionally balanced wine displays lemon, lime and a seamless spine of natural acidity leading to a finish of extraordinary length. Tasting Notes: Color: At release, the wine is a very pale green/straw colour with a slight green tinge to the edge. Nose: The wine displays vibrant lime aromas with hints of lemon and faint floral notes. Palate: The wine is quite restrained at release with a linear focus to the palate and purity of fruit flavours. Plenty of fresh lemon/lime juice characters abound with crisp and refreshing lime acidity down the mid-palate. All this is complimented by a persistent and refreshing finish. Alcohol:  12.5%

Enormously flavoursome with rich fruit characters of black cherry, plum and ripe berries. American oak adds nuances of vanilla, cigar box, coffee and toast. Tasting Notes: Color: At release, the wine has a concentrated ruby red colour with a dark purple hue to the edge. Nose: The wine has ripe and concentrated aromas of violets, dark plum and liquorice. Concentrated layers of creamy American oak complex the enticing bouquet. Palate: This is a voluptuous wine with great mid palate expression, layers of flavour and yet great balance. Fresh red berry fruits are cradled across the palate by mocha and vanilla spice flavours from high quality oak. The barrel fermentation results in a wine that has well integrated fruit and oak and harmonious, elegant flavours and a long persistent finish. Alcohol:  14.3%

The wine has intense lifted aromas of melon and white peach with underlying subtle savoury notes from the french oak. the palate delivers well-balanced and evenly distributed fruit flavours of classic melon and peach along with underlying creamy notes from the lees stirring. texturally, the wine has a retrained, tight structure overall and yet still displays a measure of subtle creaminess to the mid palate and rewards with well integrated oak. the clare valley parcel delivers mid palate fleshiness whilst the adelaide hills component contributes the restraint and elegance that are typical of this region. overall, the wine has a great palate line with length which lingers long after the wine is consumed.

This pinnacle release Shiraz is crafted from the very finest fruit selection and is entirely estate grown and bottled on the Taylor family estate in the Clare Valley, South Australia. Tasting Notes: Color: A striking, dark cherry colour which sits at the mid-point between black and ruby. Nose: Generous and immediately offers sweet, spice characters of fine oak lifting from the glass. These are underscored by fresh, red plum and cherry fruit characters that sit confidently at the heart of the wine. Palate: The palate shows considerable structure. There is much to enjoy now, with vanilla and liquorice root notes in abundance through the mid-palate and layering beautifully onto the back-palate and finish, whilst blueberry and ripe dark plums define the overall heart of the wine. The tannins have a velvety softness to them that is neither bitter nor over-firm, reminiscent of sweet plum skins and reinforcing the sense that this wine shall develop exceptionally well in the cellar. Alcohol:  14.5%

product_name: Taylors Jaraman Clare Valley Mclaren Vale Shiraz 750ml
description:
At release, the wine has a deep crimson red colour to the centre with a vibrant purple hue to the edges. there are lifted aromas of red berry and cherry fruit along with subtle black olive and spice.
this is a rich, full-bodied wine with intense flavours of ripe red berry fruit, violets and attractive oak characters of roasted coffee beans and dark chocolate.
overall, the wine is well balanced with complex, well-integrated tannins providing the palate with an intense, persistent length.

product_name: Sun Coast Roasted Macadamia Sea Salt Nuts 125g
description: These Australian grown Macadamias have been hand roasted and then gently flavoured with Sea Salt.

Nova is Starward’s signature single malt whisky which has received several global awards, but the real gold is in the bottle. Fully matured in red wine barrels, Nova is a deliciously balanced and bold whisky for sharing and mixing. Tasting notes: Nose / Like we took bright flavours of red berries and orchard fruit and coated them in soft oak spice. Palate / Imagine a rich red berry pudding covered in vanilla, caramel and spice. Finish / Balanced and long. The sweetness fades and the delicious flavour goes on. Alcohol: 41% Starward Whisky Nova 1L is Travel Exclusive Size

Fortis is a single malt Australian whisky which celebrates Australian ingredients and the red wine barrel maturation Starward is known for. The first higher ABV release for us, Fortis is matured in 100% American Oak red wine barrels to give it a fuller and richer mouthfeel.  Tasting notes: Nose / Madagascan vanilla pods, rich toasted American oak, blackberry jam, raisins, caramelised fig, over ripe plums.  Palate / Upfront vanilla, quince paste, Muscadelle raisins, chocolate ganache, cinnamon & baked banana bread.  Finish / Viscous and long, balanced with a finish of baking spices from the oak and ripe figs & raisins.  Future / Sip straight and savour. Or shake it up in a classic cocktail, like vermouth, campari and orange bitters. Alcohol: 50% Starward Whisky Fortis 1L is Travel Exclusive Size
This Malbec is full of intense dark fruit characters, a hint of plum stone and spicy notes of black pepper create a wine that is medium to full-bodied with a smooth finish. Alcohol: 14.0%

Family-owned and operated, taylors wines rests on the principle that the finest wines are those made with the greatest dedication and care. this limited edition label celebrates their heritage and the commitment of three generations of the taylor family dedicated to making fine australian wine.
nose:
plum, blackcurrant and dark cherry fruits along with a bouquet of subtle mocha and a touch of oakey spice.
palate:
plump and generous, with ripe fruit characters of plum and blackberry. mocha coffee and subtle spice from oak maturation balance the fruit flavours.

Named after the historic property first established by Scottish migrants back in 1892, the St Andrews name died when the property was sold in 1934. In 1995, the Taylor family bought the land back, producing a range of flagship wines since 1999. The Taylors St Andrews Cabernet is classic Clare, made with only quality in mind and well suited to aging for the long term, though short-term consumption is very enjoyable too we can assure you! Tasting Notes: Smell: Deep dark and brooding with hints of cassis, mint, blackberry, dried herbs, dark chocolate and cedar. Taste: Intensely concentrated and very pure with rich, ripe tannins and length to burn.  Palate: On the palate it is a very well-balanced wine with ripe blackcurrant characters intermingling harmoniously with oak characters of cedar and subtle tobacco. There is contradiction on the palate with power and strength in the varietal flavours of cassis and yet also supreme delicacy in the fine boned structure. The tasting experience is completed with long, fine tannins and a wonderful persistent presence on the finish. Alcohol:  14.2%

Dense inky black colour with a deep dark red black tinged hue. Sailing from the glass are enticing scents of red to black currant, mulberry, cedary tobacco characters, earth and mint. Rich lush blackcurrant fruits subtlety infused with mint fan out across the palate with terrific intensity. Lying underneath are notions of liquorice, vanillin cedar, tobacco, earth and spicy bay leaf elements. Beautifully integrated fine grained tannin structure with a long well endowed finish that’s both refined and classy. Alcohol:  14%

The wine has a deep and intense ruby red colour, enriched by complex and layered nose with notes of dark fruit (blackberry, black cherry), spices (pepper, cloves), and a hint of earthiness. This Shiraz shows dark berry fruit flavours of plum skin and fennel seed spice with a plush and silky mid palate core and long finely structured tannin. Stunning and vibrant drinking now, or will reward careful cellaring for ten+ years. Alcohol:  14%

A relatively new addition to the taylors range, the jaraman cabernet sauvignon is part of a range that includes some of the best in the taylors lineup of fine wines. elegant with intense fruit flavours of cherry and cassis along with hints of mint, cedar and spice.

Vibrant and invigorating, this striking wine is characterised by refined acidity, enlivened with a brisk splash of Tahitian lime, delicate floral scents, and harmonious mineral undertones, culminating in a tantalising succulence. Its vivid flavours, inherent acidity, and elegant composition are a true reflection of the age-old soils and the remarkable landscape of Skillogalee. Strikingly lively in appearance, this wine is perfect for immediate enjoyment or will enhance beautifully with careful ageing. Alcohol:  12.5%

Vibrant and invigorating, this striking wine is characterised by refined acidity, enlivened with a brisk splash of Tahitian lime, delicate floral scents, and harmonious mineral undertones, culminating in a tantalising succulence. Its vivid flavours, inher Alcohol:  13%

Bright and dynamic, this opulent wine boasts a refined acidity, enlivened by a pure burst of citrus and harmonious mineral nuances, a sharply defined structure, and a robust, rocky core. The vivid flavours, inherent acidity, and poised framework are a testament to the distinctive terroir of our age-old soil and the dramatic landscape. This wine, with its potential for over a decade of graceful maturation, promises to evolve exquisitely with thoughtful cellaring. Alcohol:  13%

Skillogalee is a small family owned winery set amongst the wooded hills in the picturesque Clare Valley. Our cool climate vineyards were planted in 1970 and range in altitude from 420 to 500 metres in altitude. A wine crafted to delight — expect lifted aromatics of bright tropical fruit with herbal spice and a gentle, juicy palate. Alcohol:  12.5%

Brimming with plush berry sweetness, this gorgeous wine weaves together a soft and approachable style with bright fruit characters. Bright, fresh flavours of dark fruit, plum, and a touch of spice, leading to a smooth and plush finish. The tannins are well-structured and to nicely balance the wine. Alcohol:  13.5%
The native yams creamy, nutty, warm and earthy flavours can be found on the Palate of Native Yam Vodka.  Alcohol: 40%
Bush Honey and Wattle seed Coffee Liqueur has chocolate on the front palate, giving way ro mocha, candied walnut and notes of honey and spiced chai on the finish. Alcohol: 23%

Deep chocolate brown with vibrant amber hues. Focused lift and intensity of spicy walnut liqueur – woody, toasty, some herbal notes too. Great intensity harnessed by citrusy acid and notes of sun dried stone fruit – nutty, spicy, terrific length. Alcohol:  22.2%

Seppelt is one of australia's most iconic sparkling shiraz's.their world first uniquely australian style of sparkling shiraz was first released in the 1890s and has since only been released in exceptional vintages. highly acclaimed by its elegance, complexity and remarkable longevity, the show sparkling shiraz is a style that's achieved countless accolades and a strong reputation as one of australia's most awarded wines.

A Celebration of Japanese craftsmanship Roku is the premium Japanese craft gin created by the House of Suntory in Osaka, Japan. Suntory has a long history of making gin. Its mastery is evident in Roku, a truly authentic and delicate gin. Carefully crafted by Japanese artisans with skillful recision and meticulous attention to detail in creating the perfect balance of flavours. 43% Alcohol

Rémy Martin XO is the signature of their Cellar Master, who with his expertise blends up to 400 different eaux-de-vie. His art of blending allows us to express the full aromatic complexity of this XO Cognac Fine Champagne. Alcohol:  40%

Rémy Martin is a family story of close to 300 years, with a visionary spirit incarnated by its unique emblem: the Centaur. Since 1724, the House of Rémy Martin has been driven by one quest - to capture the heart of Cognac: Fine Champagne Cognac. In 1985 by André Giraud, Cellar Master of the House of Rémy Martin from 1956 to 1990, decided to create an intense and complex cognac for real men: Remy Martin CLUB, presented in a very iconic bottle with 8 facets referring to the lucky number 8 in China. Juicy blood oranges have been paired with Riverland lemons and mandarins to create a loud and playful mix of citrus contrast and depth. Strawberry gum, chamomile and cinnamon myrtle enhance the floral characteristics, while local almonds and river mint also feature as part of this year’s story. Our most citrus-forward spirit yet, this vibrant, expressive gin promises to be ‘fun in a glass’, best served as a spring G&T, or as a summertime spritz. Garnish with a blood orange slice and a fresh sprig of mint. Alcohol:  44%

SHIN Classic Whisky is blended with  2 years finished whisky of ex-bourbon and ex-sherry, which are both previously aged in Japanese Shochu cask (American Oak) for a year. Nose:  fruity, slight sweet, vanilla, citrus Palate:  fresh, honey, light oakiness, orange peal, hint of white chocolate Finish:  subtle, medium finish, hint of Japanese pepper Alcohol:  40%

Juniperus is our most classical expression yet, a tribute to London Dry Gin. Our hero botanical, Juniper is distilled whole, crushed, macerated, and vapour infused to attain the highest level of complexity and depth. Grains of paradise and cassia bark add warmth and structure. Riverland citrus provides lift, softened by vanilla and macadamia, integrating the palate. This bold gin will elevate a classic Dry Martini or London Calling and make your gin & tonic sing. Here’s to a new modern classic. Alcohol:  47%

Our blend combines Shiraz, Grenache, Nero d’Avola, Chardonnay, Touriga, Mataro and Tempranillo for a bright, layered, and generous profile. The maceration and grape skins of the heavier reds adds structure, length, and deep complexity. While the Chardonnay lifts out floral notes and bright attractive aromatics. Textured and lifted, with notes of violets, elderflower, raspberries and a distinct piney juniper backbone, the perfect integration of gin botanicals and grape maceration is the key signature of this expression. Perfect in a fruit-forward Mediterranean style gin and tonic, with soda, or your favourite ginger ale. Cocktail serves include a spectacular gin sour, vibrant spritz or bramble. Alcohol:  38%

This rich, earthy Australian take on the Italian classic is a joy to behold. With less bitterness than a traditional Negroni, this blend has exceptional softness and depth of flavour. Despite sitting on a higher ABV for a Negroni, it is easy drinking, soft, well rounded and richly botanical driven, with 60 individual botanicals between its three spirit ingredients. Simply served on ice, with a twist of orange peel, it will convert anyone into an Australian Negroni lover! Alcohol: 37%

Despite its 59% ABV this spirit has made the most of the ageing process. The spirit has softened and absorbed the beautiful shiraz colour and a rich American oak and rye back-note, aged for over 18 months in barrels. This reveals the toasty and fortified bourbon flavours from deep within the oak. These flavours complement the gin’s citrus, floral and soft vanilla finish, yet with a burst of intensity, making it a spirit worthy of your finest cocktail mixes. Alcohol: 59%

A delicate, contemporary dry gin with a burst of citrus from blood orange, ruby red grapefruit and Australian native lemon myrtle leaf, balancing spice of wormwood, pink peppercorns and ginger for warmth. Herbal juniper notes lengthened by green tea, with smooth, sweet vanilla adding mouth-feel and lavender bouquet to finish. Prohibition Original is the perfect martini gin, with a soft, sophisticated elegance in flavour and depth, with a perfect balance of citrus and sweetness, spice and floral finish. Alcohol: 42%

This gin complements the rough seas, celebrating our juniper-based spirit’s naval heritage. A nose of salty ocean breeze gives way to notes of native lime interplayed by saltbush. A combination of juniper distilled through maceration and vapour infusion creates a melody of depth and mouth-feel. Sweetness and elevated texture are provided by macadamia and vanilla. The lifted finish is stormed by ginger, grapefruit and salt as the drink takes sail, three sheets to the wind. Alcohol: 58%

Prohibition Moonlight Gin is an homage to all things flourishing under the cover of darkness. A dance of flavour, florals and aromas, watch the colour-shift explode with luminescence when mixed. This bootlegger’s bouquet combines cold distilled pink lady apple with native blood limes and rare red juniper. Black goji, clove and hibiscus tease the mid palate, sandalwood nut and honeybush provides mouthfeel. Our most baroque creation yet, delivers a pink gin for those unafraid to embrace their dark side. Alcohol: 42%

A bold nose of vanilla, juniper-spice, fortified and defined by wormwood-driven herbaceous tones surrounded with a floral veil. The upfront palate is commanded by a confectionery juniper-come-aniseed flavour that stretches full, leaving a warm finish decorated with cinnamon and almond nuttiness. A rich experience Prohibition Bathtub Cut gin is as gentle as a 69% spirit could possibly be. Alcohol: 69%

Shaw & Smith is a benchmark Sauvignon Blanc. This release shows ripe tropical characters with restrained grassy notes and crisp dry acidity. Delightfully fresh lively and flavoursome. Always a classic and always quick to disappear off the shelves. Alcohol:  13%

Semi translucent bright dark crimson red colour with a crimson red hue. The nose reveals fresh dark cherry and strawberry aromas over some light toasty cedar, subtle meatiness and spice. Light weight and fresh the palate has a supple mouthfeel with flavours of dark cherries and strawberries followed by spicy cedar and a touch of meatiness on the finish. Good power wave. Slightly dryish but fine grained tannins. Long aftertaste of dark cherries, ripe strawberries and spicy cedar. Quite savoury now but will benefit greatly with more time in the bottle. Alcohol:  12.5%

Aged in French oak for fourteen months, of which one third was new – barriques and some larger format. Opaque black purple colour with a bright purple hue. Aromas of ripe blackberries and blackpepper are followed by some liquorice, subtle clove like characters and meatiness. Possessing excellent richness, power and structure the palate features mouthfilling flavours of blackberries and liquorice followed by meaty characters, spicy vanillin cedar and blackpepper whilst still retaining a refined and well toned cool climate feel. Structured yet velvet smooth tannins finishing with a long aftertaste of blackberries, liquorice, meaty pepperiness and spicy vanillin cedar.  Alcohol:  14%

Smooth, spicy notes balanced with vanilla and toffee. Sailor Jerry Ltd. produces a 92 proof spiced Navy rum featuring a quintessential Sailor Jerry hula girl on the label. Patrón tequilas are handcrafted at the Hacienda Patrón distillery in Jalisco, Mexico where people are the heart of the process - one that has remained the same since the very beginning. First, skilled jimadors uproot only the finest 100% Weber Blue Agave with the perfect sugar content and transport the heart of the plant to Hacienda Patrón. They’re then hand chopped, baked and crushed by a two-ton volcanic stone tahona wheel and a roller mill. The agave is then fermented in pine oak tanks and distilled in small batches using copper stills. Each bottle of Patrón is a work of art, meticulously inspected, hand corked and signed. Alcohol:  40%

A deep glowing copper amber color, it possesses a buttery sweet fragrance that evokes peanut brittle, cherry pie and spice. The finish is oh-so smooth with a hint of smoke laced through with a pleasant sweetness and the soft warm embrace of a fine bourbon..

Patrón Reposado is handcrafted from the finest 100% Weber Blue Agave and is carefully distilled in small batches at Hacienda Patrón distillery in Jalisco, Mexico. It’s then aged in a variety of barrels for a minimum of two months. Alcohol:  40%

Patrón Añejo is handcrafted from the finest 100% Weber Blue Agave and is carefully distilled in small batches at the Hacienda Patrón distillery in Jalisco, Mexico. It's then aged in a combination of French oak, Hungarian oak and used American whiskey barrels. Alcohol:  40%

product_name: Ralph Lauren Polo Blue Eau De Toilette 125ml
description: Polo Blue by Ralph Lauren is a Aromatic Fougere fragrance for men. Polo Bluewas launched in 2003.Top notes are melon, mandarin orange and cucumber; middle notes are basil, sage and geranium; base notes are musk, woodsy notes and suede.

Ripe blackberries/blackcurrant reduction, laced with spices - notably fennel and aniseed. Dark chocolate and cola. Familial flavours of deconstructed Black Forest cake - chocolate, custard, wild raspberry. An assortment of fresh red and black liquorice, omnipresent and even tannins. A confluence of tannin/acidity/oak/fruit  - all joyously meshed together. Turly 'alive', upon sitting and with air, all transforms. Can definitely wait. There will be ample opportunity over the next half-century.  Tasting Notes: Color: Deep, dark and bright Nose: Benchmark. Automatically recognisable - formic and glacial higher notes – not quite as audacious as a fleeting perception of heady  spirit (á la Cognac), and yet not just simple V.A. Beneath, a more familial oaked nuttiness (hazelnut?) recedes to reveal aromas of black licorice/anise/black olive. A shroud of condensed glazed fruits surrenders to reveal a fresher disposition … a coulis of berries and stone fruits; boiled beetroot. Unsurprisingly wafts of coffee-grind, pan-scrapings/jus also ascend, hovering over a persistent base of cold lamb fat and marrow. Upon sitting, a sprinkle of lavender and exotic spices almost completes the aromatic package – well, at least for another minute or  two. And then … Early days Palate: Cohesion, vigour, sheen, poise – four borders of a frame that structurally binds the lofty palate ambitions of this South Australian  blend. Fresh and balanced. Neither exaggerated nor over-ripe – lively blueberry and other youthful blue/black fruits bely the maturation timeline of this alluring blend. Certainly befitting this style, unmistakable barrel-ferment characters are undoubtedly more pronounced on palate than nose. If the mid-palate is somewhat formidable (ably supporting a thick/dense core), by contrast the back-palate is creamy and caressingly endearing. Indeed, expansive and full – washing away all ahead of it. Certainly persistent. Texturally, chewy/grainy tannins and just-right acidity abet succulence and mouthfeel. Effortlessly handles 19 months in 100% new oak. Alcohol:  14.5%

The region’s high altitude and cool climate induces riesling with great finesse and elegance with a capacity for long term cellaring. The extra hang-time allowed for terrific varietal flavour and aroma development, with the retention of racy natural acidity. A tremendous vintage for riesling. Wine Fitting: Light Bodied White Food Pairing: Seafood Alcohol: 14.5% Region: Eden Valley

product_name: Remy Martin VSOP Cognac Fine Champagne 1L
description: This is a Fine Champagne Cognac taken from the two best crus - Grande and Petite Champagne. Remy Martin's VSOP stands for elegance and richness. With its golden amber colour (old pale), smoothness and complexity, it is balanced and perfectly mature. 40% Alc./Vol.

In true bin 311 style, the vintage exhibits a concentrated fruit spectrum of citrus aromas with a mineral acid backbone. the palate offers pronounced white peach fruits with underlying sherbet and lemon. proactively rich, fresh and assertive. price may vary per state.

Penfolds bin 23 adelaide hills pinot noir has definitive earthy cherry, cooked beetroot and crushed vine leaves aromas along with subtle dustiness on the nose; softened, silky tannins with lively mixed red fruits flavours framed by nicely balanced acidity throughout impart a velvety texture that leads to a lengthy finish. Tasting Notes: Color:   Fuji-apple red Nose:   An immediate ascent of delicate white strawberry and white raspberry pastille fruits. Yes, overtly cool-climate pinot noir. Quickly following, a garnish of fresh thyme flowers and Hungarian sweet paprika. And something else, admittedly hard to identify – an aroma lying somewhere between saffron and mustard seed. If only spectrophotometer could ... !?! Oak? Perhaps a scent of star anise may be a link? Upon sitting, the faintest waft of pencil shavings confirms a definite Quercus robur or sessiliflora connection. Palate: Medium-bodied. Weight and texture no doubt positively influenced by an appealing glycerolic contribution. Felt like, rather than velvety tannins, with cherry and strawberry fruits inducing a refreshing mouth-watering/salivating grip. ‘Underneath’ - impressions of tilled wet-earth and aligned parsnip/turnip (kohlrabi) flavours. Oak imparts a structural rather than a flavour imprint – was that 17% or 0.17% new oak?! Alcohol:  14%

Bin 389 was often referred to as ‘Baby Grange’, in part because components of the wine are matured in the same barrels that held the previous vintage of Grange. This was the wine that helped forge Penfolds reputation with red wine drinkers by combining the structure of cabernet sauvignon with the richness of shiraz. Exemplifying the judicious balance of fruit and oak, Bin 389 highlights the generous mid-palate Penfolds in known for. Alcohol:  14.5%.

It has been a long wait - 28 years in the making. Placed in barrels in 1990, Penfolds Lot. 1990 Pot Distilled Single Batch Brandy has been slowly maturing for nearly three decades. Finished with a splash of Penfolds Grandfather Tawny, the result is an exceptional blend that delivers vibrancy and freshness to palate, alongside complexity, richness and indulgence. Tasting Notes: Palate: A combination of marzipan, baked figs, cardamom and cinnamon spice. Soft and round, great intensity with a warming finish Alcohol:  42%

product_name: Penfolds Cellar Reserve Grenache Shiraz Mataro Travel Exclusive 750ml
description: Penfolds Cellar Reserve wines are alternative, limited release wines that explore the innovative boundaries of viticulture, vinification and style. Penfolds Cellar Reserve Grenache Shiraz Mataro is sourced from McLaren Vale, where the maritime climate is perfect for ripening these three varietals. An approachable, fruit driven wine style that is versatile with food. Taste:  Texturally interesting, paper/pith. The ancient soils yielding notes of shale and ironstone. Pomegranate acidity provides succulence. Good rainfall in late winter and early spring provided solid foundations for canopy development and mitigated frost risk. From November to harvest it was dry, resulting in lower-than-average yields. Cool weather prevailed over summer with only one hot spell in January. Conditions were near perfect for ripening grapes to their fullest potential. Alcohol:  14.5%

Penfolds Cellar Reserve wines are alternative, limited release wines that explore the innovative boundaries of viticulture, vinification and style. This is the first release of a 100% Cellar Reserve Shiraz. The outstanding harvest afforded us an opportunity to source small parcels of high-grade shiraz to craft something different and contemporary. The Cellar Reserve Shiraz is a modern interpretation of this highly coveted varietal, showcasing the tangible benefit of blending across regions. Large format French oak puncheons and well-seasoned vats were used to mature the blend. An altogether new interpretation of our most recognised grape varietal. Pomegranate molasses entices, unfurling across the mid-palate. Mulberry leaf suggestive of cooler fruits. Slatey/granite like tannins create a well-defined and textural palate. Tightly coiled, chalky finish. Pomegranate acidity interplays with structure and texture well, everything in place, complete. Subtle oak character is detected, some spice coming through, although it’s predominantly fruit forward. Near long-term average rainfall in winter and spring provided good soil moisture profiles and encouraged canopy development, while helping to mitigated frost risk. Spring was warmer than average, with some welcome rain during September and October. From November to harvest it was generally dry and warm, with a peak temperature of 38.2°C recorded in McLaren Vale on the 27th of November. For the most part, mild weather prevailed over the summer months with only one short hot spell in January. Three consecutive days of rain in early February freshened up the vines during veraison. Mild conditions from February until harvest were optimal for slow and steady ripening of shiraz grapes. Harvest was an orderly affair, with some exceptional parcels set aside for the Cellar Reserve Shiraz. Alcohol:  14.5%

A kaleidoscope of aromas. First noted, sweet pastries, fruits of the forest and the faintest suggestion of formic acid. Max Schubert would approve. A flawless integration of the two varietals. Flavours of black and red fruit compote, cocoa powder sweetness and cold meats. Fine tannins reminiscent of oolong tea. Refreshing lift on the finish. Tasting Notes: 
 Taste:   A well-defined focus on palate. Forward facing – line and length. The fascinating interplay between cabernet sauvignon and shiraz providing not only considerable length and structure, but also width and density. Result... completely filling the palate. Always anticipated, a trademark creamy Bin 389 mid-palate. A wine with much to offer even in the flush of youth. Complexing flavours: savoury nuances of freshly sliced fennel, pan wilted radicchio leaf and pickled turnips. Moroccan lamb backstraps on eggplant relish. Red liquorice and cherry provide a sweet counterpoint. Evolved tannins seamlessly drive the palate structure. Will last many decades, if you can wait that long. Ingredients:  Cabernet Sauvignon, Shiraz Warnings:  Drink responsibly. Storage conditions:  Store in a cool dry place Alcohol:  14.5%

The vintage is a modern interpretation of this great and noble varietal, showcasing the tangible benefit of blending across complimentary regions. Large format French oak puncheons have been used to mature the blend, providing an alluring framework for the generous, varietally pure fruit. Near long-term average rainfall in winter and spring provided good soil moisture profiles and encouraged canopy development, while helping to mitigated frost risk. Spring was warmer than average, with some welcome rain during September and October. From November to harvest it was generally dry and warm, with a peak temperature of 38.2°C recorded in McLaren Vale on the 27th of November. Mild weather mostly prevailed over the summer months with only one hot spell in January. Three consecutive days of rain in early February freshened up the vines in readiness for veraison. product_name: Penfolds Reserve Bin A Adelaide Hills Chardonnay 750ml
description: Very restrained, tightly coiled. Aromas of custard apple, Granny Smiths, white nectarine, pistachios and cashew nuts. The palate has real drive, held together by a core of taught acidity. Stone fruits provide sweetness, white peaches and nectarines. Poached loquats, almond meal and freshly sliced pear.  Tasting Notes: Color:   Very pale gold with lime green hues Nose: Restrained upon first pour. Induce awakening via a sprightly decant, or vigorous swirl. Primary white peach and assorted stone fruits give way to tempting scents of fresh crème anglaise/pana cotta. Oak (just) evident, yet impressively integrated (80% new?!) Wafts of struck-match prancing above; intense, smoky barrel-ferment notes lurking below. Complexingly challenging – an abundance of character, yet not saturated; aromatically bedazzling, yet not an assault. Palate: Adelaide Hills fruit: soaring and intense white peach fruits and defined natural acidity. Barrel-ferment: an interwoven nuttiness (roasted cashew) and pliant tension. Lees contact: crème brûlée notes, volume and a heightened leesy texture. The acidity noted above is not a defining feature – more of a softer/gentler acidity playing a supporting role – complimentary to texture. An expansive palate that grows – propelled by persistent flavours and textural integrity. Alcohol:  12.5%

Bin 8 cabernet shiraz from penfolds is a red wine produced in australia on various vineyards and in several appellations (mclaren vale, barossa valley, wrattonbully, padthaway, coonawarra). the wine is aged for 12 months in french oak barrels (6% of which are new) and american (6% in new barrels). the bin 8 cabernet shiraz from penfolds consists of a blend of 52% cabernet sauvignon and 48% shiraz. the bin 8 cabernet shiraz 2014 from penfolds has a deep garnet red colour, developing aromas of blackberries and plums on the nose, which blend with more floral (purple, iris) and vanilla notes, along with hints of smoked roast beef. the wine is full-bodied and offers flavours of black fruit and white chocolate cream. the tannins are ripe and round, well framed by ageing in oak and with a complementary acidity. Alcohol:  14.5%

Complex aromatics. Baking spices and almond/croissant notes, with a struck match character - signature for Yattarna. Citrus forefront, pink grapefruit and lemon curd. Texturally fine, with hints of hazelnuts, cashews and pistachio. Braced by beautiful acidity. Tasting Notes: Color: Pale straw with green hues Nose: A complex synthesis of aromatics that take some time to fully unfurl, allow time and use a glass of generous proportions.  The first impression is a trip to a Parisian fromagerie... very ripe Brie de Meaux with lavosh and cumquat jam. There is a hint of baking spice, no doubt derived from the high-quality French oak maturation. Freshly baked almond croissant notes set the mouthwatering.  A barrel ferment struck match note is very much evident, practically a signature for Yattarna of the modern era. There is a minerality  reminiscent of razorfish or mussel shells, a suggestion of salinity that is very enticing. Palate: What the aromatics promise, the palate delivers. There is a level of complexity evident that places this vintage of Yattarna among  the finest ever made. Citrus to the fore, with pink grapefruit leading the charge, ably backed up by lemon curd. Textually very fine indeed, with a crème brûlée like richness/flavour holding court. There are flavours of just-roasted hazelnuts and salted cashews. Fresh nougat makes a cameo appearance, embedded with pistachio nuts and wrapped in glutinous rice paper. Black sesame paste baked in a Japanese milk bun. The finish is very long, the core of fruit goes on and on, braced by beautifully composed acidity. Alcohol:  12.5%

product_name: Penfolds Rwt Shiraz Barossa Valley Bin 798 750ml
description: Herald the Barossa Valley! Blue fruits at the fore - blueberry, mulberry with notes summer berry pudding. Florals of lavender and violet. Detected, cola, salted licorice and a hint of green olive brine. Powerful, opulent fruit on the palate. The tannins polished, fine and mouth filling. Flavours of crème brûlée, praline, hazelnut and fresh coffee grounds. Dark, brooding fruits add substantial weight. An epic RWT. Alcohol:  14%

A contemporary wine sees penfold's think outside the box. an alternative shiraz that is structured in french and american, new and old oak. the wine ages gracefully and can peak between the vintage year plus another 15 years. Notes of dark and purple fruits. Fresh satsuma plum and blackcurrants with sweet notes of cinnamon fruit buns. Exotic spices - juniper berries, dried rosemary, sweet paprika. A beautifully balanced wine on the palate. Sweet and savoury nuances. Sweet/tart plum, crème brûlèe creaminess. Fine and chalky tannins. Tasting Notes: Color: Dense black core. Deep purple rim Nose: Our Marananga vineyards lie in the heart of the Barossa Valley, typifying everything we love about Barossa shiraz. Such complexity! So many layers to unfurl. A distinctive ferric nose denotes the ancient Marananga ironstone, hundreds of millions of years old. Also derived from this geology, dusty graphite powder and whetstone, asphalt/hydrocarbon. A walk-through Chinatown... roast duck with plum sauce, Hoisin BBQ pork ribs. Notes of exotic spice, star anis, cardamom, pimento, acknowledging French puncheon influence Palate: As we have come to anticipate, satsuma plums and boysenberries provide a varietal/regional signature. Grippy, ripe and rich tannins anchor a tightly structured frame. Freshly sawn oak. Rye sourdough crust – still hot out of the oven. Toasted pumpkin seeds on grilled haloumi. Sarsaparilla, black cardamom pods and ethereal nutmeg spice. Alcohol:  14.5%

Bright. Alluring fruits vibrant dark black cherry meshed with crushed fresh dark plum. All laced with warm spices cinnamon & nutmeg. A great example of shiraz and cabernet weaving all together. The shiraz covertly propping up the structural underpinning and grip of cabernet sauvignon. Contented varietal notes are enhanced by an earthy vegetable and tobacco leaf imprint. Medium bodied, structurally defined, with supportive tannins (rounded, polished) and well disguised oak. Tasting Notes: Color: Crimson with purple hues Nose: Notes of graphite and a touch of walnut varnish. The nose has a distinctive blue-fruited and cranberry elegance.A complex amalgam of sweet and savoury notes emerges with a gentle swirl. Vanilla sponge with whipped cream, wet river pebbles, juniper berries and pink peppercorn all vie for attention. Palate: Very fresh and lively on the palate. Freshly cut spearmint and dried lavender. Graphite from the nose continues across the palate, emerging as structural, powdery tannins. Kalamata olives and charcuterie flavours provide a savoury sensorial experience. Sweet red fruits make for a long, memorable finish. Alcohol:  14.5%

product_name: Ralph Lauren Polo Earth Eau De Toilette 100ml
description: Ralph Lauren believes in the beauty of the earth and the importance of preserving nature. Polo Earth is a new 97% natural-origin* scent with 7 sustainable, farm-to-fragrance ingredients Bergamot Heart, Diva Lavender, Green Mandarin, Turkish Rose, Sage Heart, Haitian Vetiver and Bourbon Geranium sourced from local communities around the world. Consciously designed, Polo Earth represents the next generation of fragrance by Ralph Lauren. The Fragrance: This sheer, yet luxurious scent balances the sparkling citrus of Bergamot Heart and the vibrancy of Green Mandarin with the herbal richness of Sage Heart and the freshness of Diva Lavender Key Notes: Green Mandarin Sage Heart Diva Lavender Orange Flower The Bottle: Consciously designed and responsibly packaged. A lightweight bottle created from PCR (post-consumer recycled) glass that is refillable, featuring an FSC-certified wood cap and accented with FSC-certified paper label on the front of the bottle. FSC stands for Forest Stewardship Council and it signifies that the wood or paper product originated from a forest that was managed carefully with trees, animals, and local community benefit at heart.   How to Use:  Spray on pulse points: wrists, neck, chest, wherever you feel a heartbeat. Create a richer fragrance experience through fragrance layering by using your choice of Polo Earth Body Care products and applying Eau de Toilette as the last step.
